Disabled/flaky/slow web-platform-tests Report

A disabled test is a test that is not run, maybe because it is flaky or because the feature it is testing is not yet implemented. For WebKit and Chromium, this is denoted as "[ Skip ]" or "[ WontFix ]". For Mozilla and Edge, this is denoted as "disabled".

A flaky test is a test that gives inconsistent results, e.g., sometimes passing and sometimes failing. For Chromium and WebKit, this is denoted as "[ Pass Failure ]" (or other combinations of results).

A slow test is a test that is marked as taking a long time to run. For Chromium and WebKit, this is denoted as "[ Slow ]".

The tables below show all tests in web-platform-tests that are disabled, flaky, or slow, in 4, 3, 2, and 1 browsers. Tests that show up for more than one browser are likely to be due to issues with the tests.
